1
00:00:12,012 --> 00:00:14,181
-Good evening.
-Good evening.

2
00:00:14,264 --> 00:00:16,809
<i>Terrace House</i> is a show about
six strangers, men and women,

3
00:00:16,892 --> 00:00:18,435
6 STRANGERS, MEN AND WOMEN,
SHARE A HOUSE

4
00:00:18,519 --> 00:00:21,063
living together, and we observe
how they interact with each other.

5
00:00:21,146 --> 00:00:23,774
<i>All that we've prepared is</i>
<i>a beautiful home and automobile.</i>

6
00:00:23,857 --> 00:00:26,902
-There is no script at all.
-Yes.

7
00:00:26,985 --> 00:00:28,111
Last week--

8
00:00:28,195 --> 00:00:30,322
-There's a lot going on right now.
-There is.

9
00:00:30,405 --> 00:00:32,282
-A heart-fluttering turn of events.
-Yes.

10
00:00:32,365 --> 00:00:34,201
-The bike date was so nice.
-So nice.

11
00:00:34,284 --> 00:00:36,036
<i>-Hikaru and Misaki...</i>
<i>-Their bike date.</i>

12
00:00:36,119 --> 00:00:37,370
HIKARU OTA
MISAKI TAMORI

13
00:00:37,454 --> 00:00:39,039
<i>It was sexy.</i>

14
00:00:39,122 --> 00:00:41,750
-Are you into motorcycles now?
-I'm into them.

15
00:00:41,834 --> 00:00:43,919
-Did you have fun?
-Yeah.

16
00:00:44,002 --> 00:00:45,045
For real.

17
00:00:45,128 --> 00:00:47,464
-I laugh more when I'm with you.
-Really?

18
00:00:47,548 --> 00:00:49,424
-Yeah.
-No way.

19
00:00:49,508 --> 00:00:52,761
-And she made him hamburgers.
-She did.

20
00:00:52,845 --> 00:00:55,556
-She even cried.
-Yes, those tears!

21
00:00:55,639 --> 00:00:57,683
It was so cute.

22
00:00:57,766 --> 00:01:00,185
-This is making me want to cry.
-I'm seriously moved.

23
00:01:00,268 --> 00:01:01,478
-Why?
-I don't know.

24
00:01:01,562 --> 00:01:03,188
Why?

25
00:01:03,271 --> 00:01:04,356
What's wrong?

26
00:01:04,898 --> 00:01:07,275
-What? Why?
-I'm sorry, it's not hard.

27
00:01:07,359 --> 00:01:08,777
-No, it's not that.
-It's not hard at all.

28
00:01:08,861 --> 00:01:11,029
It's seriously good. Really good.

29
00:01:11,113 --> 00:01:12,990
-You're just relieved.
-Yeah.

30
00:01:13,907 --> 00:01:15,158
Thank you.

31
00:01:15,242 --> 00:01:18,704
-The two of them are so pure.
-Yes.

32
00:01:18,787 --> 00:01:20,873
-It's going well for them.
-Yes.

33
00:01:20,956 --> 00:01:24,459
-And Natsumi...
-She made a move on Hansan.

34
00:01:24,543 --> 00:01:26,670
She invited him fishing.

35
00:01:26,754 --> 00:01:28,380
That's right, that's right.

36
00:01:28,463 --> 00:01:29,882
I like ocean fishing.

37
00:01:29,965 --> 00:01:31,216
-In a boat?
-Yeah, a boat.

38
00:01:31,299 --> 00:01:32,676
-But from the shore is okay, too.
-Nice.

39
00:01:32,760 --> 00:01:33,761
Let's go.

40
00:01:33,844 --> 00:01:36,096
With the exams,
you're probably not in the mindset.

41
00:01:36,179 --> 00:01:37,723
Yeah, there's a lot going on.

42
00:01:37,806 --> 00:01:39,808
It'll be a reward for all your hard work.

43
00:01:39,892 --> 00:01:41,476
Yeah, let's do that.

44
00:01:41,560 --> 00:01:46,524
"After all your hard work...
I'll go out with you as a reward."

45
00:01:46,607 --> 00:01:50,068
She made a statement
that speaks highly of herself.

46
00:01:50,152 --> 00:01:52,070
She meant going fishing would be a reward.

47
00:01:52,154 --> 00:01:55,616
So it's not the fact
he gets to fish with her?

48
00:01:55,699 --> 00:01:56,825
I don't think so.

49
00:01:56,909 --> 00:01:59,286
She'd be a terrible person otherwise.

50
00:02:00,453 --> 00:02:02,873
Oh, and Arisa...

51
00:02:03,666 --> 00:02:06,251
When the exhibit is over...

52
00:02:06,334 --> 00:02:08,504
I'm thinking of leaving <i>Terrace House.</i>

53
00:02:09,755 --> 00:02:11,173
-Seriously?
-Yeah.

54
00:02:11,256 --> 00:02:13,383
I wonder if she's leaving this week.

55
00:02:13,466 --> 00:02:14,885
I wonder.

56
00:02:16,011 --> 00:02:18,055
If you were asked
to draw a clear object...

57
00:02:19,347 --> 00:02:21,559
what would you draw?

58
00:02:21,642 --> 00:02:23,644
I'd leave it empty.

59
00:02:23,727 --> 00:02:26,855
No, you have to draw something clear.

60
00:02:26,939 --> 00:02:30,067
-It's so hard.
-How about a glass?

61
00:02:30,651 --> 00:02:32,570
No, not that kind of clear.

62
00:02:32,653 --> 00:02:35,072
-Something more abstract.
-I know.

63
00:02:36,198 --> 00:02:37,700
What about your music?

64
00:02:37,783 --> 00:02:39,117
-My music?
-Sound.

65
00:02:39,201 --> 00:02:44,122
Draw something that expresses sound
without drawing notes nor instruments.

66
00:02:45,040 --> 00:02:46,333
But draw sound.

67
00:02:47,459 --> 00:02:48,544
That, I can draw.

68
00:02:49,377 --> 00:02:50,796
I don't get it.

69
00:02:50,879 --> 00:02:52,506
The music inside me.

70
00:02:53,507 --> 00:02:55,383
I thought of something!

71
00:02:55,467 --> 00:02:56,677
See ya.

72
00:02:57,553 --> 00:03:01,431
-Where are you going?
-I've got to work on my thesis.

73
00:03:01,515 --> 00:03:03,517
I have to read.

74
00:03:03,601 --> 00:03:05,435
I'll bring my drawing when I'm done.

75
00:03:10,148 --> 00:03:11,233
Don't look.

76
00:03:11,316 --> 00:03:13,902
It's nice.
It reminds me of elementary school.

77
00:03:14,903 --> 00:03:17,280
-Is that a compliment?
-Yes.

78
00:03:20,367 --> 00:03:22,745
-Hey, Hikaru?
-Yeah?

79
00:03:24,079 --> 00:03:25,998
-Will you take me out?
-What?

80
00:03:26,081 --> 00:03:27,541
Take me out somewhere.

81
00:03:28,375 --> 00:03:29,960
Take you out?

82
00:03:30,043 --> 00:03:32,921
I've been wondering
when you'd ask me out again.

83
00:03:34,590 --> 00:03:37,134
You haven't said anything.

84
00:03:37,217 --> 00:03:38,636
Yeah...

85
00:03:40,470 --> 00:03:42,890
-On your bike.
-You want to go on my bike again?

86
00:03:42,973 --> 00:03:44,808
Yeah, it was really fun.

87
00:03:46,226 --> 00:03:47,561
Yeah, but...

88
00:03:48,729 --> 00:03:50,397
You don't want to?

89
00:03:50,480 --> 00:03:52,733
No, it's not that.

90
00:03:57,404 --> 00:04:00,032
You don't seem like you want to.

91
00:04:00,533 --> 00:04:04,202
-Did you have fun before?
-Yeah, well, I like bikes.

92
00:04:05,996 --> 00:04:07,455
That's not what you're asking.

93
00:04:08,373 --> 00:04:10,292
-No, it's not.
-It was fun.

94
00:04:10,375 --> 00:04:11,502
-Really?
-It was.

95
00:04:11,585 --> 00:04:13,587
-It doesn't seem like--
-I told you I had fun, too.

96
00:04:13,671 --> 00:04:16,507
I can't tell with you.
You're a mystery to me.

97
00:04:16,590 --> 00:04:18,884
-What do you mean?
-You're a mystery.

98
00:04:18,967 --> 00:04:21,512
I can't tell what you're thinking at all.

99
00:04:25,724 --> 00:04:27,309
It's hard to know who you are.

100
00:04:28,226 --> 00:04:31,980
That means
you're thinking about me too much.

101
00:04:33,356 --> 00:04:34,983
I am?

102
00:04:35,483 --> 00:04:36,902
It's why you're reading into it too much.

103
00:04:36,985 --> 00:04:38,904
But you're obviously thinking something.

104
00:04:39,822 --> 00:04:41,406
I don't know what it is, but...

105
00:04:43,909 --> 00:04:45,703
Let's decide now then.

106
00:04:45,786 --> 00:04:47,621
Where do you want to go?

107
00:04:47,705 --> 00:04:50,207
-Anywhere specific?
-The hot springs.

108
00:04:50,290 --> 00:04:52,334
Sure, we can go to the hot springs.

109
00:04:52,417 --> 00:04:54,336
Okay, it's decided then.

110
00:04:59,550 --> 00:05:01,301
It's decided.

111
00:05:06,306 --> 00:05:09,309
DAIKAN-YAMA, TOKYO

112
00:05:14,314 --> 00:05:18,110
I wanted the girls to work on the details,

113
00:05:18,193 --> 00:05:21,321
like putting on the stickers
and wrapping the catalogues.

114
00:05:21,404 --> 00:05:24,700
-If you don't mind taking care of that?
-No problem.

115
00:05:44,637 --> 00:05:46,429
Are you on schedule, Arisa?

116
00:05:46,514 --> 00:05:49,600
-I'm catching up more every day.
-Really?

117
00:05:49,683 --> 00:05:55,564
Since everyone is helping me,
I feel like I need to work harder.

118
00:05:55,648 --> 00:05:57,608
If I were on my own...

119
00:05:57,691 --> 00:05:59,735
-You wouldn't have?
-I would've slacked in some areas.

120
00:05:59,818 --> 00:06:02,445
-Like, "Well, that's good enough."
-I see.

121
00:06:05,448 --> 00:06:06,825
Tired?

122
00:06:08,243 --> 00:06:09,662
A little.

123
00:06:09,745 --> 00:06:11,789
-It was pretty heavy.
-Yeah.

124
00:06:11,872 --> 00:06:13,331
My arms are sore.

125
00:06:14,207 --> 00:06:15,918
-I hope it goes well.
-Yeah.

126
00:06:16,001 --> 00:06:19,547
As long as Arisa says she's glad,
it went well in the end.

127
00:06:19,630 --> 00:06:21,757
Yeah, that'd be nice to hear.

128
00:06:22,841 --> 00:06:24,843
Have you talked to Nacchan lately?

129
00:06:24,927 --> 00:06:26,261
-To Nacchan?
-Yeah.

130
00:06:26,344 --> 00:06:29,014
Yeah, normal conversations. Why?

131
00:06:29,097 --> 00:06:32,142
-You heard about the fishing?
-Oh, yeah.

132
00:06:32,225 --> 00:06:35,270
She said she's going fishing with you.

133
00:06:35,353 --> 00:06:37,523
I asked her if it's just the two of you,
and she said yeah.

134
00:06:37,606 --> 00:06:41,902
I don't think I can go fishing with her.

135
00:06:41,985 --> 00:06:45,405
-The two of you? Oh, you don't want to.
-Yeah, I don't want to.

136
00:06:47,032 --> 00:06:51,537
I gave my girlfriend
a gift the other day,

137
00:06:51,620 --> 00:06:54,915
a fishing rod and reel,

138
00:06:54,998 --> 00:06:57,585
and I told her we should go fishing.

139
00:06:57,668 --> 00:07:00,588
But I live here,
so I haven't been able to take her.

140
00:07:00,671 --> 00:07:04,174
So if I go fishing now, it would look bad.

141
00:07:04,257 --> 00:07:07,385
-It would be the worst.
-I think I should cancel the fishing trip.

142
00:07:07,469 --> 00:07:12,516
I feel that, knowing Nacchan,
I think it's better to make things clear

143
00:07:12,600 --> 00:07:16,186
rather than just pretend
it didn't happen.

144
00:07:17,020 --> 00:07:19,481
Has your girlfriend said anything?

145
00:07:19,565 --> 00:07:21,233
She said she misses me.

146
00:07:21,316 --> 00:07:22,985
-That's it?
-Yeah.

147
00:07:23,068 --> 00:07:26,238
She hasn't tried to stop you?
Like, "I can't take it"?

148
00:07:26,321 --> 00:07:29,032
She might be thinking it,
but she'd never say it.

149
00:07:30,450 --> 00:07:32,620
At my place the other day...

150
00:07:32,703 --> 00:07:35,122
I mean the studio...

151
00:07:35,205 --> 00:07:38,501
When I was working on
the mock-up for Arisa,

152
00:07:38,584 --> 00:07:41,253
or rather, the model for her...

153
00:07:41,336 --> 00:07:43,421
my girlfriend came over,
so I asked her to help.

154
00:07:43,506 --> 00:07:46,008
She said,
"No, I refuse to help with that."

155
00:07:46,884 --> 00:07:48,343
-'Cause it's for Arisa?
-Yeah.

156
00:07:48,426 --> 00:07:49,469
Crazy.

157
00:07:49,553 --> 00:07:52,097
-Yeah.
-So she was jealous.

158
00:07:52,180 --> 00:07:53,516
You guys are lovey-dovey then?

159
00:07:55,142 --> 00:07:57,603
I'm not really sure.

160
00:07:59,980 --> 00:08:04,527
There are three women in closer vicinity
than my girlfriend right now.

161
00:08:04,610 --> 00:08:06,403
It's hard to ignore.

162
00:08:06,486 --> 00:08:11,867
The moment I find myself
attracted to any of them...

163
00:08:11,950 --> 00:08:14,161
in my mind, that's cheating.

164
00:08:15,453 --> 00:08:17,706
If that happened,
I'd probably break it off.

165
00:08:17,790 --> 00:08:19,625
-If it were you, you wouldn't tell her?
-Who?

166
00:08:19,708 --> 00:08:22,044
-To your girlfriend, I mean.
-I wouldn't.

167
00:08:22,127 --> 00:08:25,213
Not at that point anyway.

168
00:08:32,721 --> 00:08:33,722
Yes?

169
00:08:35,599 --> 00:08:38,060
-Can I come in?
-Sure!

170
00:08:39,019 --> 00:08:40,854
-Are you by yourself?
-Yes.

171
00:08:40,938 --> 00:08:42,773
-Oh, good.
-Good?

172
00:08:42,856 --> 00:08:45,108
-I wanted to talk to you.
-What is it?

173
00:08:46,694 --> 00:08:49,112
-Can I sit here?
-Yes.

174
00:08:49,196 --> 00:08:52,407
-What we talked about the other day...
-What we talked about?

175
00:08:52,490 --> 00:08:54,743
-About going fishing?
-Oh, yes.

176
00:08:54,827 --> 00:08:56,537
-Well...
-Yes?

177
00:08:58,121 --> 00:09:01,834
I can't go fishing with you
if it's just the two of us.

178
00:09:02,835 --> 00:09:05,588
-I can't.
-Okay.

179
00:09:05,671 --> 00:09:07,590
I had promised my girlfriend...

180
00:09:07,673 --> 00:09:09,424
-What do you mean?
-That I'd go fishing with her.

181
00:09:09,508 --> 00:09:11,760
I had promised her,
but hadn't taken her yet.

182
00:09:12,553 --> 00:09:13,637
Oh, I see.

183
00:09:13,721 --> 00:09:17,349
So I don't think
I should go fishing with you.

184
00:09:17,432 --> 00:09:18,642
-Yeah.
-Okay.

185
00:09:18,726 --> 00:09:23,438
But like you said,
I would like to talk with you more.

186
00:09:23,522 --> 00:09:24,857
Okay.

187
00:09:24,940 --> 00:09:29,277
-Since we haven't talked much.
-Yeah.

188
00:09:29,361 --> 00:09:31,655
So...
What's wrong?

189
00:09:31,739 --> 00:09:32,990
Oh...

190
00:09:37,160 --> 00:09:38,954
It's nothing.

191
00:09:39,037 --> 00:09:40,372
And?

192
00:09:41,582 --> 00:09:45,002
-What's wrong?
-Nothing. Don't take it the wrong way.

193
00:09:45,085 --> 00:09:48,839
I'm sorry.
I had other things on my mind.

194
00:09:50,007 --> 00:09:52,843
I thought maybe
you'd like to go out to eat sometime?

195
00:09:52,926 --> 00:09:55,679
-I came to ask you out.
-Thank you.

196
00:09:55,763 --> 00:09:57,848
You did? Thank you.

197
00:09:58,849 --> 00:10:02,060
I'm almost done with my work right now.

198
00:10:02,895 --> 00:10:04,229
So, afterwards.

199
00:10:05,438 --> 00:10:06,732
Okay.

200
00:10:07,775 --> 00:10:10,402
Are you okay?
Something's bothering you.

201
00:10:10,485 --> 00:10:12,863
Yeah, I am.

202
00:10:13,697 --> 00:10:15,658
Store it for now.

203
00:10:16,158 --> 00:10:19,369
-I don't know if I can anymore.
-I'll...

204
00:10:20,663 --> 00:10:22,790
I'll lend you my ear.

205
00:10:26,293 --> 00:10:28,420
I don't know if I can help, but...

206
00:10:33,008 --> 00:10:34,927
Why are you crying?

207
00:10:35,010 --> 00:10:37,596
-Why are you crying now?
-I don't know.

208
00:10:38,597 --> 00:10:40,766
-What is it?
-I don't know.

209
00:10:40,849 --> 00:10:43,519
I don't understand
what I've been feeling lately.

210
00:10:45,896 --> 00:10:47,731
Let's go now.

211
00:10:47,815 --> 00:10:49,357
Let's get a drink.

212
00:10:49,441 --> 00:10:51,443
-Right now?
-Yeah, let's go now.

213
00:10:51,527 --> 00:10:52,611
Okay.

214
00:10:53,904 --> 00:10:55,906
-That makes me so happy.
-Let's go.

215
00:10:57,616 --> 00:10:59,367
It's an emergency.

216
00:10:59,451 --> 00:11:02,705
Now I feel like drinking.
Let's go.

217
00:11:07,751 --> 00:11:09,086
Thank you.

218
00:11:30,649 --> 00:11:33,401
ARMAN BITARAF, 25 YEARS OLD,
ASPIRING FIREFIGHTER

219
00:11:33,485 --> 00:11:36,404
ARISA OHATA, 25 YEARS OLD,
HAT DESIGNER

220
00:11:36,488 --> 00:11:39,533
HIKARU OTA, 19 YEARS OLD,
MODEL, CONSTRUCTION WORKER

221
00:11:39,617 --> 00:11:42,494
NATSUMI SAITO, 26 YEARS OLD,
MODEL, ASPIRING ACTRESS

222
00:11:42,578 --> 00:11:45,706
YUTO HANDA, 27 YEARS OLD,
4TH YEAR AT TOKYO UNIVERSITY OF THE ARTS

223
00:11:45,789 --> 00:11:49,251
MISAKI TAMORI, 23 YEARS OLD,
ASPIRING ENTERTAINER, PART-TIMER

224
00:11:56,675 --> 00:11:59,595
EBISU, TOKYO

225
00:11:59,678 --> 00:12:02,598
TEPPAN BUAISOU

226
00:12:02,681 --> 00:12:05,684
What's going on?
Seriously.

227
00:12:06,769 --> 00:12:09,354
When I came to <i>Terrace House...</i>

228
00:12:10,355 --> 00:12:15,736
in the beginning, I'd speak my mind

229
00:12:15,819 --> 00:12:18,781
without really taking others
into consideration.

230
00:12:19,322 --> 00:12:24,995
I used to do that
without really worrying about others.

231
00:12:26,038 --> 00:12:29,750
But after everything
that happened with Minori

232
00:12:29,833 --> 00:12:36,131
and after I realized
how different other people are from me,

233
00:12:36,214 --> 00:12:41,386
I couldn't really speak my mind anymore.

234
00:12:43,764 --> 00:12:46,183
It's been really tough for me lately.

235
00:12:47,434 --> 00:12:48,686
I see.

236
00:12:48,769 --> 00:12:51,522
So when you said
you couldn't go fishing...

237
00:12:52,981 --> 00:12:55,233
it felt like, "Now you, too?"

238
00:12:57,485 --> 00:13:00,238
Not to say you were my last hope.

239
00:13:00,906 --> 00:13:06,787
But at least with you,
I wanted things to be honest.

240
00:13:06,870 --> 00:13:09,582
So when you said you couldn't...

241
00:13:10,248 --> 00:13:12,960
I felt a little overwhelmed.

242
00:13:13,460 --> 00:13:16,338
And it all came pouring out.

243
00:13:18,465 --> 00:13:21,635
-I'm sorry.
-No, it's okay.

244
00:13:21,719 --> 00:13:23,053
But...

245
00:13:23,136 --> 00:13:26,932
What do you want to say?

246
00:13:27,015 --> 00:13:29,351
You said you can't really speak
your mind anymore.

247
00:13:29,434 --> 00:13:32,521
What sort of things are on your mind?

248
00:13:33,021 --> 00:13:36,191
I've never been really good
at smiling for the sake of politeness.

249
00:13:37,275 --> 00:13:43,448
